Reasoning: The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of reconfiguration problems, which are related to optimization problems on graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CC seem to be the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the study of algorithms and complexity. However, the paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to cs.CG and cs.DM. Finally, the mention of maximization problems suggests a connection to cs.GT.
